flavor_text_entries.red:
A POKéMON that
was resurrected
from a fossil found in what was
once the ocean
floor eons ago.
flavor_text_entries.blue:
A POKéMON that
was resurrected
from a fossil found in what was
once the ocean
floor eons ago.
flavor_text_entries.yellow:
A POKéMON that was
recovered from a
fossil. It uses the eyes on its
back while hiding
on the sea floor.
flavor_text_entries.gold:
On rare occasions,
some have been
found as fossils which they became
while hiding on
the ocean floor.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
This POKéMON lived
in ancient times.
On rare occasions, it has been
discovered as a
living fossil.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
Three hundred
million years ago,
it hid on the sea floor. It also has
eyes on its back
that glow.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
KABUTO is a POKéMON that has been
regenerated from a fossil. However, in
extremely rare cases, living examples have been discovered.
The POKéMON has not changed at all for
300 million years.

This Pokémon thrived 300 million years ago. It’s
said that living specimens can still be seen
in a certain region—a rare sight.

hard shell.

flavor_text_entries.sword:
This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto
molt every three days, making their shells harder
and harder.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
While some say this species has gone extinct,
Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common
in some places.
